      <akn:section eId="sec_28:2A_204">
        <akn:num>28:2A-204</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Formation in general.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_28:2A-204_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A lease contract may be made in any manner sufficient to show agreement, including conduct by both parties which recognizes the existence of a lease contract.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_28:2A-204_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>An agreement sufficient to constitute a lease contract may be found although the moment of its making is undetermined.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_28:2A-204_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Although one or more terms are left open, a lease contract does not fail for indefiniteness if the parties have intended to make a lease contract and there is a reasonably certain basis for giving an appropriate remedy.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
